2. USB Boot Protocol
================================================================================

The Ingenic USB boot protocol used to USB-boot U-Boot onto a device was
determined through clean-room reverse engineering of USB traffic between Ingenic
devices and the vendor tool, using standard USB analysis tools (Wireshark,
USBPcap). This was done for the purpose of hardware interoperability, which is
permitted under:

  - U.S. Copyright Act §117 and DMCA §1201(f) (interoperability exception)
  - EU Software Directive 2009/24/EC, Article 6 (decompilation for interoperability)

The USB vendor request codes and bulk transfer protocol are functional
interfaces required to communicate with Ingenic SoC hardware. Functional
interfaces are not copyrightable (Lotus v. Borland, Oracle v. Google). Flashing
itself uses the standard USB DFU 1.1 class implemented by mainline U-Boot.

================================================================================
3. Firmware Binaries (firmware/dfu/)
================================================================================

The SPL/TPL and U-Boot binaries in the firmware/dfu/ directory are compiled from
Das U-Boot (the gtxaspec/u-boot isvp_<soc>_usbboot defconfigs), which is licensed
under the GNU General Public License version 2 (GPL-2.0). These binaries are
redistributed under the terms of GPL-2.0.

These binaries run on the target Ingenic SoC during the bootstrap process.
They are not executed on the host computer.

